      • getUVSphereTriangleInteriorAngle

        public static double getUVSphereTriangleInteriorAngle(int s)

        A UV sphere approximates a real sphere by using a fixed number of vertical segments. When using 8 segments, for example, the sphere looks like an octagon when viewed from above. This function returns the interior angle, in radians, of one of the triangles that make up the shape.

        The following always holds: 2 * Ï€ = n * getUVSphereTriangleInteriorAngle(n)

        Parameters:
        s - The number of segments
        Returns:
        The interior angle of one of the resulting triangles
